text: According to the lady, lady finger is consider meat, brinjal is also consider meat. Stew vegetables is also consider meat dish. Becareful with your orders. Was charged $4.20 with 3 pcs of brinjal btw. Wow. There were not much vegetables selection also at 6pm on a Saturday. I was a frequent here and I guess this is the last time I'll get anything from this economical vegetables mixed rice stall.

Came to try the new vegeterian stall yi su pin after i saw big john jiak's reels. We ordered a chicken rice and bak kut teh and also takeaway crispy chop kolo mee. Chicken rice were just okay. I had nicer one somewhere before. Bak kut teh not bad. A bit pity, kolo mee is soggy, not sure is it takeaway or overcooked. Crispy chop taste like the meat chicken cutlet.
